= Distros are OSes based on the Linux kernel and are multiple instances of Linux designed for different purposes and end users
= They have the same components, architecture and philosophy but offer their own unique products, services, packages, UI, tools etc.
= Linux distros are widely used as it is a secure, stable and reliable OS with regular updates. For cyber, since it's open source, we can customise our distrro to configure it for specific uses

Debian as an OS:

= Debian is another Linux distro, known for its stability and reliability
= It uses the apt (Advanced Package Tool) package managed system to handle updates and patches
= One of the most flexible and customisable distros, providing excellent system control to the user
= Strong committment to privacy and security, receiving regular updates. Useful for cyber
